        "verdict": "needs-attention",
        "topFinding": "POST /api/transactions/bulk-delete (apps/api/src/server.ts:534-544) hard-deletes transaction rows with a bare DELETE and takes no snapshot first, while every other destructive path in the codebase does: import, rollback, Plaid takeover commit and Plaid restore all call createBackup and fail 503 on snapshot error. It is wired to the Transactions page multi-select behind a confirm dialog whose own text reads \"This can't be undone (apart from restoring from a backup)\", and that promised backup may not exist: pruneOldBackups (backup.ts:100-116) deletes every snapshot older than 30 days with no keep-newest-N floor, so booting after a month away can prune the backup directory to empty. Three lenses reached this independently. The finding is not new (open as a MEDIUM for four runs, already queued as bar-raise-2026-07-04-yab-bulk-delete-no-backup) but the severity re-grade is: an unguarded permanent delete of a user's financial records is a data-loss exposure, which sets the verdict to needs-attention rather than working. No code regressed; HEAD is unchanged at 2be93d7 since 2026-07-06 and the tree is clean. The score drops this run come from deeper inspection, chiefly the proof that bar-raise silently dropped 6 of 9 open findings on the way to the work queue. The fix for all of it is one attended Budget release; every queue item is auto_safe:false so the automated drain cannot close any of them.",
